%N A396188 Index of 2^n in A394166, or -1 if 2^n does not appear.
%C A396188 It is a strong conjecture that every power of 2 appears in A394166.
%C A396188 Since A394166 is infinite, it certainly contains terms t >= 2^k for every k. And the first time a term t >= 2^k appears that term t will equal 2^m for some m >= k.  So A394166 contains infinitely many powers of 2. But does it contain every power of 2? That seems less clear. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jun 04 2026
